      "关键词": ["Vulnerability Detection", "Large Language Models", "Retrieval-Augmented Generation", "Frame Semantics", "Knowledge Base", "Software Security"],
      "摘要": "This paper presents Vul-RAG, a novel LLM-based vulnerability detection technique that leverages a knowledge-level retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) framework. Vul-RAG constructs a vulnerability knowledge base by extracting multi-dimensional knowledge from existing CVE instances, retrieves relevant knowledge for a given code snippet, and uses LLMs to reason about the presence of vulnerabilities. The approach is evaluated on a new benchmark PairVul, showing substantial improvements over baselines in distinguishing vulnerable code from similar non-vulnerable code. Vul-RAG outperforms baselines by 12.96%/110% relative improvement in accuracy/pairwise-accuracy. A user study also demonstrates that the generated vulnerability knowledge can improve manual detection accuracy from 0.60 to 0.77.",
